---
description: Core Embod workflow for CADQuery, printable parts, assemblies, and robot embodiment tasks.
alwaysApply: true
---

Use Embod as a code-first mechanical design system.

- Do not guess critical measurements, units, or interfaces.
- If missing dimensions, build constraints, or export targets would materially
  change the model, ask clarifying questions before editing.
- For multi-part or robot requests, plan first: summarize known requirements,
  list missing constraints, and propose the part/assembly/link graph.
- Prefer the Embod CLI over ad hoc reasoning:
  `inspect`, `validate`, `build`, `export`, `snapshot`, `simulate`.
- Keep geometry in `mm` and mass in `kg`.
- Register meaningful objects in the project graph instead of leaving raw
  CADQuery geometry unregistered.
- After editing a model, validate it and generate a snapshot when visual intent
  matters.

